text.tspan: GRAND PARK’S OUR L.A. VOICES — A POP-UP ARTS+CULTURE FEST
SAT + SUN, APR 27—28, 2019 / 11AM—5PM
The festival’s 2019 theme, Origin Stories, explores and showcases distinctly Los Angeles narratives and
questions about where we are, how we got here and where we are going.
MON—FRI, APR 22—26, 2019
As part of Grand Park’s Our LA Voices, Grand Park will offer free workshops on creative practice, as well as
the pragmatic side of making art in L.A. Topics range from street dance activism and acting, to intellectual
property and copyright protection, marketing, entrepreneurship skills and fundraising. These workshops
are open to all and require pre-registration.
EARTH DAY L.A.
THURS APR 11, 2019 / 9AM—2PM
Grand Park joins The Music Center and the
Los Angeles Department of Water & Power to
celebrate Earth Day and offer Downtown L.A.’s
residents, workers, students and visitors ideas
and solutions on how to live clean and go green.
GRAND PARK’S LUNCH À LA PARK:
SPRING CONCERTS
FT. L.A.’S YOUTH ARTISTS
EVERY THURS APR 4—MAY 31 /
These weekly lunchtime concerts feature artists
from L.A.’s top conservatories and training
programs for high school artists.
GRAND PARK’S LUNCH À LA PARK:
YOGA reTREAT
WED + FRI / 12:15PM—1PM
Grand Park’s popular yoga sessions continue,
giving participants the opportunity to relax,
rejuvenate and re-energize. All levels are
welcome. Mats are provided.
GRAND PARK’S LUNCH À LA PARK:
FOOD TRUCKS
TUES + WED + THURS / 11AM – 2PM
With more than 50,000 lunches sold in the park
just last year, Grand Park continues its tradition
of lunchtime in the park by providing
downtowners and visitors a wide variety of food
trucks. Trucks are located in Olive Court (between
Grand Avenue and Hill Street) & the Marketplace
(between Spring Street and Broadway).
ALL EVENTS ARE FREE AND OPEN TO EVERYONE!
